column13:
Judy-Judy is currently struggling. She had not been feeling well recently. Finally went into have some blood test done and found out her thyroid is not functioning properly. She has not spoken to the doctor but thinks it could be hypothyroidism and is afraid of the new disease. The fear was crippling such that she was not even able to read her Bible yesterday which has been a ritual for her. The group gave her words of encouragement reminding her that fear is a sign of Satan not a God who is of love and the Holy Spirit will protect her. She was not able to stay on the call because she was not feeling well and we all will continue to pray for her and give her strength through this difficult time.

Susan- gave us a praise report. She recently had her third chemo therapy session. After the first and second sessions are counts dramatically decreased from 144 to 25 after this first session and 10 after the second session. She was waiting to see what it is going to be after this session. She still has some issues with her mouth and food but appears better. She has been having issues lately with sleep and also a history of restless legs. Sometime she watches movies and other times she may be up cleaning. Usually drinking a cup of decaf coffee with cream or milk helps but she finds that she has been lactose intolerant and have been trying to avoid dairy. Makes exception when she can’t sleep. Ask the group for any suggestions regarding sleep. Suggestions included  types of tea such as sleepy time plus lavender products. Meditation and reading also suggested.

Sydney- Recently experienced spinal pain. Had a visit and provider gave her steroids which she does not like. In the past she has had back within muscle relaxer and try to get that prescribed by her neurologist but never heard back from them. Ended up speaking to another provider who prescribed Norco which she did not want but went to the pharmacy anyway to pick it up and found out the back with and had been filled by her neurologist. Perplexed why she was not notified of this but happy to get it in her back is much improved. The neurologist also scheduled her for her MRI and waiting for the results. Continues to try to adjust to a new neurologist. She continues to consume caffeine containing beverages multiple per day even though she’s not working. We discussed the health benefits of consumption of that much caffeine. She also has not completed her school project which now she has an ultimatum to turn it in by Monday or she will get no credit. Sydney is trying to get 100% credit trying to talk to the course Director almost daily who is getting annoyed with her. Encouraged Sydney to make a decision and do the submit button as soon as possible so that can be over and she can get on with her degree and life.

Maya- She is preparing for surgery but will be done after her birthday. Wants to know if she will be able to drive. We counseled  her again about resting after any type of surgery and not trying to do things like she had before hospitalizations. Her doctors remarked that she is walking better so they want to test her nerve sometime in the future because they are shocked since she had so much nerve damage in the past.
There has been a lot of stress and her family. Her daughter has been harassed by her ex-husband‘s wife lately especially on social media. Next month will be a court case and she will be 18 soon. Your daughter wants to leave San Diego area. Mom and other family live in orange county and thinking about going up there but Maya really doesn’t want to. Also it appears that they want to drop the case that she was trying to file against her ex-husband feeling it was not worthy of pursuing.

Nikki- it was great to see her again. She continues to have a very hard time with everything. It is overwhelming at best. She is battling probably over 30 different doctor and their associated tests. She is also trying to help her son who was recently diagnosed with lupus besides Hashimoto’s thyroid disease and a few other things. He’s only 21 and hard to grasp the severity of his illness. They do not have a great relationship as there is some resentment because of Niki‘s previous history of alcoholism. Trying to deal with their relationship as well as issue their chronic illnesses has been tough. At this time she feels like she is in a dark place barely hanging on but she is faithful and knows God is good. We continue to uplift Niki and reinforce that God is good and has a plan. He will never leave or for sake her. Sydney shared that she had gone through some of the same things both Niki and her son had when she was young and she’s willing to speak to her son if he desires.

column13:
Sydney-having some issues with her nephew going to school and having to drop him off at the entrance to the school rather than his classroom per Covid protocol. She is also having issues with her new neurologist. Some of their conversations makes her suspect if this is the right specialist for her. It appears she is dictating her healthcare plan rather than the new specialist. Also feels the neurologist either isn’t writing certain things down to remember their previous conversation or is distracted unlike her previous neurologist. She has not gotten her Covid vaccination yet because they are planning chemotherapy early May. 

Susan - Is doing a little bit better today. Her mouth sores have improved. She is a little tired today after working with a  person who comes in to assist her with house chores. Today that person helped go through some books.
She will have her third chemo treatment on Monday. Not sure when she will be able to get out even for a support group meeting if we start seeing each other in person. It will depend on her white blood cell count levels.

Delores- feels better since her granddaughter has re-entered into school five days a week from 9 to 3. That gives her a break and hopefully her granddaughter will be more productive. She continues  to have a joint problem especially her knees. Was told to do some x-rays and to follow up with the doctor regarding injections. Has gained weight especially during the Covid. And knows that weight I s contributing to her pain. Admits that she had gained weight, secondary to food choices

Maya- she is contemplating the removal of her gallbladder next month. Trying to hold off until after her birthday when she will turn 40. She is also trying to return to the workforce after she has recovered from gallbladder surgery. Thinks she will try to go back into the insurance business like she had before since she can  make pretty decent money in order to support her and her daughter without the financial added stress
Her daughter seems to be doing pretty well

column14:
Healing Prayer, Discussion topics from Endurance- Anger, Fear, Anxiety, then we talked about what God says about it. You say, it's impossible, God says All things are possible-Luke 18:27, you say, I'm too tired, God says, I will give you rest- Matthew 11:28-30, You say, I can't go on, God says, My grace is sufficient- 2 Corinthians 12:9, You say, I can't manage, God says, I'll supply all your needs-Philippians 4:19, You say, I'm worried, God says, Cast all your cares on Me- 1Peter 5:7
Psalm 91:4 Take refuge under God's wing
He will hold your hand through the valleys and walk you through your trial. All things are possible with God.

column13:
Brittan-recently celebrated her birthday. She was able to go out with family to an Italian restaurant in Lakeside. She had been there before and shared a pasta dish with her mother since they give big portions. Because it was her birthday she was able to get complementary cannoli but she also wanted cheesecake. In general her health is a little on the upswing. Still mourning the loss of mom‘s dog. Her mom did like the scripture that was sent but she still sometimes goes back into a kind of a depression. Brittan also mourning the loss because that signaled the time when she was diagnosed with her multiple sclerosis. She is also trying to get her Covid vaccination but so far no luck. Brittan asked for prayer for the grieving of her mothers dog and overall getting of appointment for the Covid vaccine soon.

Judy-is happy at this time because she received her first Covid vaccine today. Overall she’s been doing pretty well and does not have any complaints. She has not been in contact with other family than her mother. Judy does have two other siblings but they have young kids at home. Judy has not done her bloodwork yet.

Susan- she is new to our support group. Looking for group she can share how she is . Grew up catholic. Does not really study the Bible. She has recurrent ovarian carcinoma that came bake last month.The first time she was diagnosed and went through treatment was in the 1990s. Chemotherapy treatment is different this time than before. She has developed some mouth sores which has made it difficult to eat certain foods. Susan tends to cook for herself. Had a catering business in the Bay Area years ago.Looking for any type of support.

Delores- has been doing ok in general. Spoke about health appointments.  Still has back and leg pains. Granddaughter doing ok. Anxiety has not changed

We talked about what cancer CAN NOT do! It can not cripple  love, can not separate us from God, can not corrode faith, can not destroy peace, can not kill friendships.
We talked about what God CAN do! HE CAN PROVIDE HOPE, FAITH, LOVE, PEACE, COURAGE, and these things are eternal.

2 Corithians 4:8-9, 16-18, 2 Corinthians 1:3-4, 1 Corinthians 15:57, Romans 8:37, Hebrews 13:5, Philippians 4:6-13, Joshua 1:9, Isaiah 41:10, 2 Corinthian 12:9

Reliving what her supervisor had said is she did not have the skills for the job. Receive encouragement from her mother but it took a while for it to sink in and her to start thinking about the future. Plans to continue finishing her degree. She has one more class to complete.  Sydney also happy that she was able to see her regular dentist this week.

Niki - has a praise report first that she was able to get a car. Quit driving after getting DUI ‘s for a while. Had quit praying about it and periodically used her mother’s once in a while. She continues to have issues with her health. Currently she is doing a little bit better regarding her mental state and stamina.  Still has pain issues. Takes advantage when she’s able to feel a little better to accomplish more things.  Still searching for the right primary care provider. Nikki has been concentrating on helping her son and his health

Judy- Has been having trouble with groceries. Amazon Fresh messed up her order or does not use the EBT account and messes with her finances. 
She has not seen granddaughter lately. Did not get to lab for blood tests yet. 

Delores- She continues to have anxiety issues. Went to a pain doctor primary referred to her who has problems. Told her license issues and cannot prescribe medication for her. Still wants prayer.

column13:
Brittan- currently she is having problems with communication between her self and neurologist. She has unexplained electric shocks mainly in her arms that neurologist does not think is MS related but primary care provider thinks it is. Tried to get second opinion neurologist but that’s far nobody wants to see her since she already has a neurologist. Brittan will continue to try to obtain a second opinion neurology consultation. She recently started back doing physical therapy again after about a month. Brittan went today and had a good session. The therapist will try to also figure out what might be causing her electric shocks. Brittan has a rescue dog which is been a tremendous help to her over the past few years. She has felt a little bit better that she started to spend time reading as well as staying busy by trying to cook and bake when she is able. The family typically takes turns cooking dinner. Both her and her sister find a lot of recipes on the Food Network site.

Maya-Has had some stress related to still getting jerked around regarding Social Security award/money disbursement. Also got some “devastating news quote regarding gallbladder polyp that had enlarged and possibly if got larger could signal maybe even gallbladder cancer. Will have another ultrasound in three months to reassess. She thought her health was getting better after her hysterectomy since she was no longer anemic and her white blood cell count has improved. Not sure if she could take another surgery mentally as she had hoped to go back to work soon because financially needs to have income coming in. Try ring to prepare for her daughter to graduate high school and go to College.

Delores- Has been having some increased anxiety manifested as breaking out in a rash? Hives while waiting in lobby full of people in lab area. Took a few days for symptoms to result. Still has issues with her health and not ready to get the vaccine for Covid yet. Ella her granddaughter seems to be doing OK at this time. Denies any other issues.

column13:
Brittan- she was very appreciative that we had change the meeting time to seven so she could attend. Has been going through a lot in the past year mainly related to depression and some anxiety. Did not want to bother anybody about her troubles. She is still mourning the loss of one of her best friends who died about a year ago around the time of her birthday. Has questions about whether or not her friend will remember her when she is up in heaven. Continues to have issues with communication and her family like no one understands or hears what she says. Her doctor advised her to stay at home and so she really goes out except to the store quickly. Because of one incident where she went down the wrong aisle and people were complaining not realizing there were arrows on the floor.

Nikki-Today is a little bit better for her. She is in the kitchen preparing dinner but she usually tries to do most of the time and she’s able. She continues to have her health issues that wax and wane in  severity. Memory is still not great and she prefers text rather than speaking on the phone because sometimes she may forget the conversation but the text she can always go back and then respond. Still having problems with eating and will have her esophagus dilated soon and hopefully able to eat more.

Maya -ask for prayer because she still has not received any Social Security in six months. As far as her laboratory tests are concerned she continues to have a low white blood cell count and protein in the kidney what’s the doctors are watching. Her daughter attended the group with her virtually and had a lot to discuss. She will be graduating from high school in which she is in rolled in middle school college. Plans to go to a holistic college in La Jolla and become a massage therapist and be able to also do acupuncture. Ultimate goal is to own her own business. She should graduate in May but at the same time she could start early in the holistic college in May as well if she desires but think she will take three months off to relax.

Judy- Has been doing OK but was not able to continue babysitting her granddaughter who is now in daycare. Realized it took a lot of energy to watch an infant. Your mother is still very cautious regarding the virus and has not taken the patient anywhere lately. Due to have some blood test done at UCSD sometime in the near future.

Delores- continues to stay inside for the most part. Had her granddaughter clean out her closet and has a lot of clothes and shoes to donate if anybody needs any. Age appropriate clothes for 10 to 13-year-old and Niki volunteered she knew of a family that might be able to utilize these clothes and shoes. Asked for prayer for her daughter and grandson getting back together again. They have court tomorrow

Support group here to help with individual burdens 
Psalm 91:1-12 read out loud to them but can read the whole chapter

column13:
Sydney-Sydney describes having a dental procedure done today in preparation for crown. Currently has a temporary place by Dentist who was a little intense. Apologizes for possibly speaking a little funny. Had a mixup with another appointment she was supposed to have this afternoon but it has been decided that she will go tomorrow before work. Continues to have some stressors in life related to family and health issues. Does admit to some brain fog as well as achy bones and told probably related to her nerves being inflamed.

Jennifer - States that she is very sick at this time and ask for prayer.  Did not want to go into thing more than that this evening but understanding about what a lot of the support group member’s were experiencing . Participated in the support group until nearly the end and then had to leave

Nikki- she continues to struggle both mentally and physically with her health. Has been to various specialist and still cannot pinpoint some of her symptoms. Still looking for a primary care provider but has found someone she will meet with agrees to temporarily help manage her condition with various specialist. Gets frustrated, depressed and feels like she is losing her mind and alone in her journey at times. Has difficulty finding the words to express herself or even speaking. Sometimes her body gets stiff and does not want to move. Continues to have issues with family communication/interaction. Because of this she tries to keep to her self more isolated.

Maya- Currently She’s having mixed emotions regarding her sister who is in a coma. Her sister suffered a brain bleed secondary to an aneurysm burst . Sister remains in a probable coma. Had often on relationships with sister who had time it was not very kind and actually mean to her as well as her children by saying spiteful things. Mentioned  thatHer sister never change the way she was including eating habits after the first time she had issues with aneurysm or stroke. Maya is trying to be more plant-based because she knows that is better for her health and her kidney function which is decreased secondary to Lupus. Concerned about daughter graduating in June and not being able to participate in the usual senior outings because of Covid. Everyone gave various suggestions about alternatives but also pray that hopefully by June things will turn around and she might be able to participate in something for the   grads. 
Received one penny for child support that’s far. Waiting on disability and currently used stimulus check to pay off rent and some of her debt.

Norma- after trying to go back to work for two weeks she realized that was not going to be viable. She had only worked four days out of the two weeks and supervisor has threatened she might lose her job. Doctor put her out on disability two days ago. Patient has not started chemotherapy yet. Worried about side effects after talking to different people.  Also worried about how she’s going to pay for her chemotherapy I assume if she does not have a job.  Relative died from Covid in the LA area.Gave her words of encouragement.

Delores- overall everything is about the same. Still dealing with accident that occurred three years ago in her complex. Lawyer wants her to continue with therapy and follow up with specialist regarding possible surgery on her neck.  A cousin’s wife recently passed away from Covid. She asked that we keep her cousin  in our prayers

Norma-norma continues to struggle since her breast cancer surgery. She was having a lot of pain from the procedure plus fearfulness and decreased self-worth. Currently the pain is significantly decreased.She has been lifted up by our support group members and others feeling better about her situation and her being a child of God. She only asked for continued prayer.

Judy- has been doing fairly well overall. Does not mention incapacitated pain or major depression like before. She has had more interaction with her granddaughter and will be going up to her daughters house in the coming week to help babysit. Daughter is working from home so she will be around even though Judy will be the principal caregiver during the day. She will also get to spend time with family during this holiday season which is great as in previous years that was not the case.

Maya-has been doing a little bit better. Try not to overdo it. Has some issues with her ex and upcoming court date scheduled in January which adds more stress to her life and her daughters. Maya is attached to her daughter’s service dog more than herdaughter at this time. I think the reason is because she tends to feed and walk the dog daily. Plus the dog also sleeps in her room. It is good companionship. Still on the quest looking for cauliflower orange chicken from Trader Joe’s. Has been to at least five different locations without finding it.

column13:
Delores- has not been feeling well lately. She has decided to do a Covid test with her granddaughter tomorrow. Does not think she really has a disease because she does not go out but wants to be sure. Did not feel like celebrating Thanksgiving this year. Her son brought over some food that they made but it was not to her liking. Plans to have the energy to do a Christmas dinner however. Her daughter from North Carolina might also come out. Still stressed over the chain of events related to her grandson. Issues with granddaughter Ella persists. Having joint pains and may get injection sometime in the future. Just asks for prayer.

Maya-she is struggling because Worker’s Comp. has not been providing her with monetary assistance. Looks like she will need to find a lawyer. He’s had issues with food availability. Has been doing more  both at home and also doing some deliveries which she is not supposed to do for 6 to 8 weeks after the surgery. She was spotting. Her doctor mentioned it was because she was doing things she should not be doing during this time of recuperation. Felt like she was caught in between because they had no income. As it is she is able to pay rent but that’s about it. She is stressed over not being able to pay other bills. It was mentioned that she might have resources available and I will check on rock cancer care and get back to her.

column13:
Delores-she is having issues related to family. Her grandson age 12 tried to commit suicide by drinking some Drano but he just rolled around in his mouth. Her daughter felecia was arrested for child abuse because she did not take him to the hospital but she did call poison control. Her daughter was released but still has a court date in January and cannot be in contact with her son at this time. Delores had thought about trying to bring him back to California but realize that would not be a good idea nor would she be able to handle him if he acted up. She continues to stay pretty much at home. No major changes in her health otherwise.

Sydney -is having some issues with work and for the first time was written up. Getting into the holiday season she needs the restrictions so that they will not work her more than she should because would cause too fatigued.Sydney recently celebrated her birthday which she enjoyed with her best friend. Still having issues with her dad’s wife as they’ve been clashing for years.

Judy- She said she’s been doing pretty well health wise. A little sad that she used to be active in ministries until COVID. Does not do well with Zoom meeting. Sydney-States this is getting to be the busiest time of the year at Macy’s where she works. Sometimes she bears the brunt of  customers complaining.  She has noted more anxiety lately. Had an anxiety reaction when she was in the bank. Face timing mom when that occurred and one employee tried to get into the conversation. Had multiple people including two or three bank employees try to talk to her and even one of them placed their hand on her shoulder. Another got into her personal space. She ended up leaving. Sydney will end up meeting a new neurologist soon since her FMLA expires next week . Also  work related restrictions paperwork expires soon too. She needs that because you’re going from 8 to 10 hour days.

Debra - Recently lost her husband to cancer and they have a 12-year-old son Vincent. Initially wanted husband to attend and she thought about volunteering. Things went downhill fast when he had recurrence and was taken home-around 6 weeks. She’s looking for support and will soon get counseling for both herself and her son through hospice. Taking it day by day. Has some family support. She lost her job during the Covid period but hopes to go back to work sometime soon.

Delores- having issue with East County teens getting together. It was advise to contact CH campus. Has been pretty much to herself.  Ella sometimes has the wrong attitude. She recently went up to Rancho Cucamonga again and did MRI. She does not have any upcoming appointments

column13:
Nikki- Has been going through a lot lately. Recently her family had a Covid scare. Her nephew’s girlfriend was in contact with somebody who tested positive. The girlfriend has been coming in and out of where she lives. Niki will have a Covid test performed tomorrow. Currently she is in quarantine and had to cancel a lot of her appointments which he is bummed about. Some of the things she had to cancel included an MRI as well as OT and PT appointments. She sees her health is deteriorating. She does not have the energy/stamina to do a lot of the things she used to do especially around the house. Her  hands don’t seem to function the way they should and is contemplating cutting her hair because of this. Does not feel social and  has been staying pretty much to herself lately. Gets frustrated because she’s not able to do things around the house and other family members are not picking up the slack so it doesn’t get done. Trying to rely on God and reading more scripture in a different way to understand what is supposed to mean to her.

Judy-has been doing pretty good lately. She learned how to order groceries online through Amazon. Judy is expecting a delivery today and the good thing about it is delivery occur on the same day of the order.  Feels good she does not have to rely on others. Her  granddaughter is still beautiful but no direct contact. 

Delores- has been doing pretty well. Family came down to visit her this past weekend and she overdid it by walking more than she normally would. They went out to dinner downtown and later she went out to the store. Now her joints and legs are more swollen than normal. Also a little leery of being exposed since she was out in the public more than she had been for sometime. 

Maya- has been doing pretty well but busy trying to make sure everything is in order before she has surgery on November 4. It was nice that her neighbor helped out with some cat food recently and she had just gone to Walmart for more cat food tonight. She is concerned because she was advised not to do anything for six weeks which is very hard for her. She is used to providing and not used to relying on others.

Now there is hope that she can learn and be able to lead a better life.  She still has to undergo some more testing but thankful that nothing serious has been found thus far.

Delores-she has been doing pretty well. Depression seems to wax and wane. She provided the group with some Resources that are available. She’s able to get produce and if anybody needs any she’s going to help or give them some based on one of the programs. She was told that she was going to have surgery on her throat problem within two days which really stressed her out because she has to get prepared for things like this. She spoke to them and it has been postponed considering  the pandemic.

Sydney-has been a little stressed out lately as the roll out to return to work is being contemplated. She’s had contact with her boss who wants me to come back even if she has to be in the back and not amongst the public. Sydney does not like being in the back isolated. 
Oncologist wants her to start chemotherapy in June. She still has a couple weeks of school she has to complete it does not want to start therapy since it may interfere with her ability to complete her best work for school and we need to talk to their office more about this
Dad relationship still not good. . Had conversation with  her dad‘s wife related to when she was 16.  Ask the wife to judge her not when she was a teenager but how she is now 10 years later

Maya-recently celebrated her birthday but decided to bless one of her friends and went to their house providing goodies. Told us the story about her friend and what she’s overcome since she was 16 years old and essentially abandoned. 
She continues to do a lot of work and then has paid for it by her joints really causing problems. The rheumatologist has put her back on the lupus medicine but not seeing any effect yet
Maya  has also been stressed to ex husband and his threats to her and her daughter. Tried to give encouragement and remind her that God  is in control and her ex does not have any strong hold over her or her daughter

Nikki- She continues to have health issues. Has a lot of pain. Despite not going or doing her usual activities she still is quite busy. Her primary care provider close the office. She could  not go to the genetics appointment what she was looking forward to as it will have to be rescheduled sometime in the future after the pandemic is  over. She’s in the process of making her own supplements and hopes this will improve your health 

Judy-continues to struggle with pain. Tried to get up and walk but paid the price afterward. Seems to be more tired sleeping and taking naps during the day which he never used to do before.

Maya-continues to struggle with multiple types of pain. She has shingles pain, abdominal appendix pain as well as lupus issues. Just got her period which adds pelvic pain. Takes oxycodone which she does not want to stay on very long and her doctor advised her to restart gabapentin. No is suffering from a little migraine too. 

Sydney-Mom just got out of the hospital today. Patient late to our meeting because she had to pick up soup for her mother from Trader Joe’s. Patient has been having flareups of her MS as well as some anxiety. Recently moved a couple weeks ago at the same time Mom went into the hospital. Had been trying to do some things around the house in order for it to sell. Had some sibling rivalry between one brother accusing the other and mentioned he would try to kill the other brother. The same brother also try to convince her that MS was her fault. We all tried to tell her if facilitator also as mentioned on Sunday that this talk was from the devil/Satan and there was nothing to fear.

Jennifer – first of all has a praise report that there is no evidence of cancer anywhere. She was able to go through one  CT scan almost without being  pre pre medicated. Let the department know and had to be rescheduled but found out no signs of cancer. She has another scan scheduled but leery because thyroid cancer is associated with increased radiation exposure. MRI might be an alternative. Also worried about daughter’s depression. We will pray for her and her daughter

Jennifer-she had been struggling to get her procedures scheduled but has met with a specialist since our last meeting, They want to do a procedure in a couple of days but she is unsure because of the COVID -19 as well as not being explained exactly what will take place as she is supposed to work that day. She said she will continue to pray about it as she has been, and we all agreed we would pray for each other.

column13:
Roxanna-Roxanna is currently about to start chemotherapy for  stomach cancer tomorrow.. She’s been undergoing various test and appears to be localized with some lymph node involvement. Roxanna had a second opinion at UCSD where her sister works for an oncologist who specializes in G.I. cancers. She was told that the treatment plan she was advised through her insurance which is Kaiser is correct which made her feel better. Her mom is going to move in with her to try to help during this time although her mother cannot drive and has her own issues so it will be an adjustment for both. Patient has the option of going out on disability or working periodically and she will play it by ear depending on how she feels with the treatment.

Sydney-has continued to have issues with nerve pain. She tries to work around it but has had to try to isolate herself from the customers and work in the back during this past week. Sydney has noted some hair loss which was pointed out to her by her father multiple times which made her feel really badSuch that she missed work which she never does. Her mother helped her change her hair.  Mom even went out and cut her hair short like her. Sydney felt much better after that

Maya-currently out on disability after a fall  and suffering a concussion. She continues to have issues with pain. She is having some issues related to her ex-husband and the effects it’s caused on her daughter. Her daughter talked a long time about what she’s been going through in her life suffering from post traumatic stress disorder and recently it’s gotten worse with her dad-threatens To have her go back to her old school. Even though he’s not able to do that because he does not have custody and it was already decided in court her daughter remains fearful because she loves her new school. Through the new school she’s been able to volunteer at Sharp and wants to get into the medical field

Judy-She continues to have issues with memory, pain in seizures prevent her from driving. Her mother takes her everywhere even though she has friends who have volunteered to help her. Mom appears to be overbearing even going to her mental health appointments in sitting in for the first half of it describing what’s transpired in the past month. Judy would like to change this in hopes to not have her mother be so overbearing. May discuss this with mother or during the next counseling session with both the counselor and mother together

Delores- Recently had her garage broken into and now just getting  the locks put back on. Had to move some of her valuable stuff out of the garage into her house. Patient continues to go to doctors appointments. Continues to get confused with what they say and when she tries to press them to write it down was told recently she would have to pay for information just to have an idea of how many steroid injection she’s having her knees. Delores is also worried about her granddaughter and her friends. Trying to decide which is the best middle school for her to attend.

Advised to come in to talk about the results. Does not have transportation to come in on Friday. One of the other participants in this support group volunteered  to drive her to the appointment on Friday so she does not have to wait until next week to find out what’s going on.

 Sydney discussed her ongoing issues with work, Her supervisor and other employees. Sometimes she feels down and tries to put up a friend she can do anything because she does not want sympathy.  Jennifer we found out in a previous time she used to be a clown as a side job. Today she was able to make a figure of balloons in honor of Sydney‘s birthday a couple weeks ago. She continues to struggle with her health and had some issues with levels of her thyroid. She is still cold however to be a part of this ministry and do more administrative things for rock Cancer care.

column13:
Dawn D - this was her first time coming to the group. Her husband and mother both have cancer and she is taking care of them. Her husband is not responding well to the medicine, and has started to have conversations about dying. They have a 4 year old, and she is trying to finish up her Social Work degree at the same time. Does not have a support system, but sees a therapist regularly.

Deloris - still trying to find another doctor. Having trouble controlling and managing pain.

Sydney - they thought she was having an appendicitis attack, but there is an infection in her gut that has developed from immune system being compromised because of the chemo. Working out things at work, customers and other coworkers are saying unkind things about her appearance and mannerisms.

Jenn - having more tests done, the tiredness that she felt when she was initially diagnosed with thyroid cancer are starting to come back. Going in for more bloodwork, did not get a conclusive result from the last one. Worried about work, as she is the only adult and primary source of finances in her home.

Crystal - spoke with via telephone. Will not be coming to group for awhile, its a hour and a half travel time round trip, she homeschools her children and also leads the Girl Scout Troop for her daughter, so it is a lot in the middle of the week. I let her know that we would continue to check in with her, pray for her, and would like to call periodically during our support group times so the other members can hear her, and she can stay connected.
column14:
Spent time getting to know Dawn, she shared where she it at, why she feels she needs/wants a support group. The other members shared a bit of the things that they were going through that also led them to the group and what has kept them coming. 

The topic was "BUT GOD". Speaking on every emotion that is being felt is valid and is part the personal journey, but its not the end. There is always a "but God" because He is bigger that every medicine, side effect, prognosis, fear, etc. Asked each member to share their biggest struggle at the moment, but to finish the sentence with "but God" and share what God is doing in and through them.

Priscilla Shrier has a sermon called "Who's Your Daddy?" at the end of group everyone closed their eyes and I read it as I prayed over them.
column16:
* Amber delivered a meal to Dawn on 7/21/19 and Kathleen has been contacted to make cookies for them as well.

*The name of the book is "Peace in the Face of Cancer" by Lynn Eib. 

*There is one for caregivers called "Soul Care for Caregivers" by Susanne West that might be a good one for family members

*I am going to try an organize a get together for the members in the group to meet for dinner/coffee on one of the off Wednesdays.

Sharing about ways to get involved, how God has and will use each one of ours stories for His glory. Talked about the gifts in 1 Corinthians and I shared a speech by Stuart Scott that he gave about being alone and fighting.

column14:
*letting our natural emotions come to surface
* what is the TRUTH about what we may feel 
*how to acknowledge and handle a crisis of faith -- what does that look like for you?
*reframing our thoughts to what we are grateful for, especially during a moment in which the feelings you have are exactly the opposite
*read Ephesians 1 over the group, gave some context as to what was happening when Paul wrote the letter, and then shared how in looking at your identity in Christ, God has bestowed blessings on you that were predestined and He knew that this day was going to be here, and to trust Him means to trust all of Him.

column14: Why do bad things happen, and what do we do after they happen.  These were the topics and for many of us from different levels of our experience we were able to discuss that God is in charge and we must continue to trust.  With that trust also comes the responsibility of sharing our emotions with God and not feeling like we have to hold anything back on how we feel with God.  Its ok to feel mad, angry, sad, alone, but its so important to know we have a God that loves us and will always be with us.
column16:

column13:
Stephen Porter - Our brother is currently struggling with the thoughts of having to go through chemo and radiation next Tuesday starting his second battle with cancer.  He will have his PICC line inserted on Monday.  He doesn't understand why this has happened to him again and felt alone.  We immediately lifted him up in prayer and let him know we are here for him and most importantly God is here for him.  It was after our prayers that he became very grateful and seemed to have more of a peace as we continued in the group session.  
He told his co workers and family about his cancer and is taking the steps in his life to prepare for his treatments.  He is requesting a ride for Tuesday after his treatment and said he is going to get the forms filled out so we can receive our services.  
Prayer request:  Is to be able to make all his appointments and not get sick from the chemo treatments. 

Joey-  He gave some encouraging words to Stephen and thanked him for coming to the group and showing so much strength.  Joey is still going to school and seeking Gods guidance as to where He wants him to serve in life.   
Prayer Request :  To continue doing good in school, and to get his car fixed.

Eugene- He gave a very inspirational and heartfelt prayer for Stephen.  Eugene is doing good and always blessed to be at the group.  
Prayer Request:  Continue strength in serving, his ex wife find God and help in growing their relationship to what God wills it to be, and for his daughter who is getting ready to deploy.

column13:
Vanessa Claudio vannessa.claudio@live.com 619-495-1574
Vanessa is a cancer survivor who was diagnosed when she was 19 years old in the late 90's.  She described how doctors couldn't figure out what was wrong when she first got sick but an X-ray to the chest reveled the mass that she was cured from through treatment.  She was going through college at the time and describes the hardship of having to stop school and endure something that at that time was not really well known.  She wished there was a cancer care support group when she was diagnosed because she felt so alone and never really got the support she needed.  She had a relapsed twice with the cancer and through treatment beat it both times.  Now she is a nurse married with two beautiful children and husband wanting to do more with helping people with cancer.  It was a pleasure having her at the support group, and from our conversation it was evident she was happy to connect to people who have endured the hardships of cancer and know the feelings that come with it.


Edward Claudio  claudioedward@yahoo.com  619-421-8092
Edward is Vanessa's husband and huge supporter of his wife helping people with cancer.  He was very emotional during the support group about his wife being a cancer survivor and opened up about his cousin Danny who  he lost to cancer when he was a teenager in the mid 90's.  Vanessa didn't realize how impacted her husband was by the lost of his cousin until he opened up at the group.  Edward described seeing his cousin endure the pains of the treatments and saying goodbye and how he thought about killing himself after his cousin died so he wouldn't be alone.  There was a lot of pain Edward held inside about his cousin Danny and I was blessed to have been able to listen to him as he opened his heart.  Edward has a heart to help those with cancer and will be praying about what direction he should go, weather its to volunteer with cancer care or helping out his wife where he can.

Lizeth is my wife who doesn't normally go to the groups because she is still having a difficult time with everything that has happened to our family when our daughter got cancer, but decided to join us today.  She gave her testimony and shared some of her pains that cancer brought to our lives and continues to bring.  She has come a long way in being able to open up about our lives, but I know she still has a lot of healing to do and I pray God continues to guide me in helping her in any way I can.
column14:

Edward brought up the encouragement of the book of Romans and gave testimony of what God has done in his life and his wife.

column13:
Eugene talked about his daughter being in Paris France when the terrorist attacks accord.  She was on a college group trip traveling from England to France.  The night of the attacks Eugene's daughter described to him how a student invited her and a few other students to a concert but she decided not to go.  Later that night they heard gun fire a few blocks down and ran for their lives.  Eugene was contacted by the US embassy in France that night letting him know his daughter was safe but that she was not able to go home because France closed off all its borders.  Eugene opened up about the anxaity of not knowing if his daughter was safe when he first heard about the attacks and wanting to go down there and bring her home but having to wait.  His daughter is back home and doing better now but the student that went to the concert was killed in the attack.  The only thing we know is she was from Long Beach, Ca.  Many prayers for this young girl who lost her life and the many victims from the attack.  
On the way out after the meeting we ran into a cleaning staff member who asked what were about and opened up about how his son use to have cancer and currently his wife has cancer.  We lifted him up in prayer and invited him to come to the support group next week.
column14: Trusting in God and not letting our emotions get the best of us.
column16: Though we have not gotten any patience this month God has been guiding many people in our direction at the end of our meetings.

column13: It continues to be me and Eugene at the support group praying and  reflecting on how cancer has affected our lives.  It wasn't until the end of the group tonight when we were about to leave that a member of another ministry came to check on a computer in the library and opened up about his dad having cancer.   We gave our testimony and lifted him up in prayer.
column14: Discussion was perseverance under trial and tribulation.  Scripture shared James 1:3 "because you know that the testing of your faith produces perseverance."

column13:
Heather: Doing well but very sad about all the stuff going on with our group. 
RoseMary: Worried about her husband that is getting scan results on Wednesday.
Jan: Received bad news yesterday regarding her cancer spreading outside of her liver.
Crystal: Worried about her Grandma and what the doctors told her that they can't do anything else for her and that she is too weak. 
Chris: Just trying to be there for Crystal and Jan. It gets hard and he seemed very quite.
Jen (me)
Anita: She is homeless and attending group tonight. She was asking about free food and wanted to see if she could talk to someone about vouchers. She has breast cancer and needs help.  I gave her the number to RCC so she can call and speak to someone.
column14: We prayed for everyone in our group. We discussed our week since our last meeting. We said special prayers for Jennifer Nash who is in the hospital and the doctors don't think she will make it to the weekend. We all talked about our favorite scripture.

column13:
Eugene is currently is a long time volunteer who is currently in need of prayer for his marriage.  He is currently going through a divorce, which was filed by his wife but he is still keeping the faith and trusting in God that He will lead him in the right direction.   

Andrew is  a cancer patient Eugene has been in contact with giving support and prayer through email and phone.  In the third week of October Andrew was facing a financial crisis in which he was going to be short on rent $1,000.  Andrew felt helpless not being able to help his family because of his condition and asked for prayer.  
God is good because last week Andrew contacted Eugene and let us know God answered his prayer and medical claim he has been waiting for came through and produced enough money to keep Andrew and his family going.  Prayer request is for better health and support for his family.

Debbie is a prior volunteer who has lost a few family member to cancer and ex husband was a cancer survivor.  She has had to leave the group for the past few months but I have kept in contact via email and phone.  She is in need of prayer because of a previous marriage that has ended with her husband relapsing in drugs and becoming violent.  Debbie's husband  is currently behind bars and she is going through the court system to make sure he gets the help needed there.  She asked for prayer in protection and guidance.  

I was gone since the beginning of September to October traveling from San Diego to L.A by foot carrying a cross spreading the Gospel raising awareness for children with cancer.   It feels good to be back but I have been spiritually attacked since the end of my journey, and am asking for prayer in continually seeking what God wants and putting Him first in my life.  My daughter who is a cancer survivor is struggling with her PTSD from what she went through when she had cancer.  I ask for prayer that she gets better, and that God uses us to help others.
column14:
2 Timothy 1:7 "For God hath not given us the spirit of fear; but of power, and of love, and of a sound mind."

Trusting in God and knowing that He is in charge and no matter how bad life gets He does all things good.
